517
00:29:20,843 --> 00:29:22,790
You're on the other side now,
so...

518
00:29:23,164 --> 00:29:25,218
how am I ever gonna get
a serious answer from you?

519
00:29:25,219 --> 00:29:26,799
Hey, Jesse! Come here.

520
00:29:27,266 --> 00:29:31,752
- I am on your side.
- No, you're not.

521
00:29:32,779 --> 00:29:34,455
You're not even my mother.

522
00:29:35,564 --> 00:29:38,054
Your husband killed you.

523
00:29:38,055 --> 00:29:40,623
So do me a favor.
Okay, Mariel?

524
00:29:40,624 --> 00:29:44,198
Do me a favor
and-and-and stop pretending

525
00:29:44,199 --> 00:29:47,537
that anything's ever
gonna be the way it was again.

526
00:29:48,534 --> 00:29:50,099
Because it can't be.

527
00:29:52,394 --> 00:29:53,939
You're not my mother.

528
00:30:09,758 --> 00:30:12,477
You may find what I'm about
to show you disturbing.

529
00:30:13,536 --> 00:30:16,196
But I promise,
we're all patriots here.

530
00:30:27,593 --> 00:30:30,545
I've seen those boxes before
at the site of your downed...

531
00:30:31,532 --> 00:30:32,815
chopper.

532
00:30:38,063 --> 00:30:40,042
Would you like to know
what's in them?

533
00:30:40,746 --> 00:30:43,690
Sergeant, could you bring one
down to the lab for us, please?

534
00:30:48,824 --> 00:30:52,681
Did you know
those two kids that Szura shot?

535
00:30:52,905 --> 00:30:54,039
Not really.

536
00:30:55,879 --> 00:30:58,209
The young woman
was pregnant.

537
00:30:58,663 --> 00:31:00,697
Why would he kill
a pregnant woman?

538
00:31:00,698 --> 00:31:03,247
If his goal
is to build a majority,

539
00:31:03,248 --> 00:31:05,770
wouldn't he want all the people
here having babies?

540
00:31:05,771 --> 00:31:07,151
Yeah.

541
00:31:07,395 --> 00:31:09,451
That might not be
on his timetable right now.

542
00:31:09,907 --> 00:31:11,040
Or Underlay's.

543
00:31:12,589 --> 00:31:15,359
It's hard to lead an army while
you're pushing a baby carriage.

544
00:31:15,434 --> 00:31:16,656
Hey, they're here.

545
00:31:21,249 --> 00:31:22,533
Why are there two boats?

546
00:31:25,070 --> 00:31:26,472
Who's that guy
in the little one?

547
00:31:36,284 --> 00:31:37,447
Szura.

548
00:31:45,165 --> 00:31:46,477
How long has
this operation been running?

549
00:31:46,478 --> 00:31:48,529
Since '96.

550
00:31:49,518 --> 00:31:52,067
That's the same year
your plane crashed, isn't it?

551
00:31:53,446 --> 00:31:56,537
So you've been aware of these
changes in people since '96?

552
00:31:56,540 --> 00:31:57,539
Well, not at this level.

553
00:31:57,540 --> 00:31:59,150
It's grown over time.

554
00:31:59,314 --> 00:32:01,743
With each new hurricane,
we've learned more.

555
00:32:02,207 --> 00:32:04,290
But when we found the crew
from this weather plane

556
00:32:04,291 --> 00:32:07,550
and discovered that
they were all still alive...

557
00:32:08,568 --> 00:32:11,440
well, you can imagine
how excited we were.

558
00:32:54,166 --> 00:32:55,340
Oh, my god.

559
00:33:07,522 --> 00:33:09,044
What are you doing
with them?

560
00:33:09,691 --> 00:33:11,014
Testing them.

561
00:33:11,670 --> 00:33:13,236
And they've been
incredible.

562
00:33:13,813 --> 00:33:16,692
They've shown
reMarkable resiliency.

563
00:33:17,812 --> 00:33:19,958
Like you,
after the shooting.

564
00:33:21,901 --> 00:33:24,130
They really are
amazing creatures.

565
00:33:27,487 --> 00:33:29,162
They aren't "creatures."

566
00:33:29,215 --> 00:33:30,449
I'm sorry, Tom.

567
00:33:30,945 --> 00:33:32,679
I meant no disrespect.

568
00:33:33,999 --> 00:33:36,103
A lot of our funding
has gone into testing,

569
00:33:36,104 --> 00:33:38,558
but even more
has gone into cleanup.

570
00:33:38,660 --> 00:33:40,583
In order to keep a project
of this size under wraps,

571
00:33:40,584 --> 00:33:42,579
we've had to cover
a lot of ground.

572
00:33:43,093 --> 00:33:45,567
And... as I guess you know,

573
00:33:45,568 --> 00:33:49,048
each new being leaves
a rather large footprint.

574
00:34:02,785 --> 00:34:04,290
Thank you, sergeant.

575
00:34:06,998 --> 00:34:09,354
It's a lot to comprehend,
isn't it?

576
00:34:11,617 --> 00:34:14,713
So you knew
about me since '96?

577
00:34:15,339 --> 00:34:18,138
No, we just
found out recently.

578
00:34:19,929 --> 00:34:22,669
I've always considered you
a loyal partner, Tom.

579
00:34:23,254 --> 00:34:23,871
But you have to understand

580
00:34:23,872 --> 00:34:27,452
why certain factions wouldn't
want to bring you into this.

581
00:34:27,586 --> 00:34:29,059
What factions?

582
00:34:29,414 --> 00:34:31,659
Just know that everything
that is happening here

583
00:34:31,660 --> 00:34:35,924
is in the best interest
of the american people
and your community.

584
00:34:35,925 --> 00:34:39,278
I am my community. What
factions are you talking about?

585
00:34:40,075 --> 00:34:44,394
The ones that would have you in here,
if you push this.

586
00:34:59,879 --> 00:35:01,727
- You mr. Varon?
- Yeah.

587
00:35:02,152 --> 00:35:03,059
We got your call.

588
00:35:03,060 --> 00:35:04,761
What are you doing
with him?

589
00:35:05,376 --> 00:35:08,048
We picked mr. Dennison up
on the other side of the island.

590
00:35:08,049 --> 00:35:08,882
"Dennison"?

591
00:35:08,883 --> 00:35:10,484
Murder's a pretty
serious charge, sir.

592
00:35:10,485 --> 00:35:12,223
And if one of his people
has committed a crime-

593
00:35:12,224 --> 00:35:13,783
He committed the crime.

594
00:35:14,632 --> 00:35:15,419
His name's not Dennison.

595
00:35:15,420 --> 00:35:16,839
It's Szura.

596
00:35:17,344 --> 00:35:18,653
I'm afraid
you're wrong about that, sir.

597
00:35:18,654 --> 00:35:20,474
Mr. Dennison
runs a relief center here

598
00:35:20,475 --> 00:35:22,607
for the victims
of the recent storm.

599
00:35:23,138 --> 00:35:26,562
Were you a victim
of the recent storm, lieutenant?

600
00:35:30,734 --> 00:35:33,214
Where are these bodies
you called in about?

601
00:35:44,581 --> 00:35:45,815
They were right here.

602
00:35:49,997 --> 00:35:51,601
They were right here!

603
00:35:53,262 --> 00:35:54,467
You know, ranger,

604
00:35:54,950 --> 00:35:56,351
I think the best thing
you can do right now

605
00:35:56,352 --> 00:35:59,888
is to go home, take care
of your family and just let

606
00:35:59,889 --> 00:36:02,986
the people who know what's best
for the community do their jobs.

607
00:36:07,189 --> 00:36:08,974
What community is that?

608
00:36:11,259 --> 00:36:12,554
What community?

609
00:36:12,555 --> 00:36:15,043
The community that supports
the killing of innocent people?

610
00:36:16,102 --> 00:36:18,557
The community that would take
a mother away
from her own children?

611
00:36:18,558 --> 00:36:20,252
That community?

612
00:36:20,253 --> 00:36:22,067
A community like him?

613
00:36:22,200 --> 00:36:24,399
Are you like him,
or are you just on his payroll?

614
00:36:24,804 --> 00:36:27,050
Because either way,
you're no better than he is.

615
00:36:31,295 --> 00:36:34,096
Will you be needing
an escort, mr. Varon?

616
00:36:34,973 --> 00:36:36,778
Why don't you let him
come with us?

617
00:36:37,184 --> 00:36:38,527
It's all right, Russell.

618
00:36:40,047 --> 00:36:42,998
Whatever happens,
it's all right.

619
00:37:05,670 --> 00:37:07,917
So, father...

620
00:37:08,805 --> 00:37:12,621
perhaps you'd like
to stop by my house
for a little confessional.

621
00:37:18,512 --> 00:37:20,873
Mrs. Wade says you're doing
very well in spelling.

622
00:37:20,874 --> 00:37:21,912
- Yeah.
- Yeah?

623
00:37:21,913 --> 00:37:22,956
And I got
all my words right.

624
00:37:22,957 --> 00:37:24,286
All your words?

625
00:37:25,485 --> 00:37:27,944
The hardest one is
"united states,"

626
00:37:28,139 --> 00:37:30,184
because it's actually
two words.

627
00:37:30,670 --> 00:37:31,856
That's great, Rose.

628
00:37:31,857 --> 00:37:34,014
I bet your dad is
gonna be so proud of you.

629
00:37:36,861 --> 00:37:38,073
What was that?

630
00:37:39,704 --> 00:37:44,091
Rosie, I want you to go inside
and wait for me, okay?

631
00:37:44,106 --> 00:37:45,991
And I will be right there.

632
00:38:07,527 --> 00:38:08,962
Jesse?

633
00:38:10,421 --> 00:38:11,998
What are you doing?

634
00:38:11,999 --> 00:38:13,463
Shooting.

635
00:38:15,456 --> 00:38:17,111
I'm not too good, but...

636
00:38:20,228 --> 00:38:22,096
Where did you get
that gun?

637
00:38:22,962 --> 00:38:24,627
Daddy Tom.

638
00:38:25,805 --> 00:38:27,240
Tom gave you that?

639
00:38:29,453 --> 00:38:30,496
Yeah.

640
00:38:30,539 --> 00:38:32,163
Wasn't he thoughtful?

641
00:38:35,048 --> 00:38:36,483
You've been in a fight.

642
00:38:37,522 --> 00:38:39,246
And you've been drinking.

643
00:38:42,206 --> 00:38:43,728
What are you shooting at?

644
00:39:06,330 --> 00:39:08,196
These are pictures
of your family.

645
00:39:08,691 --> 00:39:10,116
Not my family.

646
00:39:10,410 --> 00:39:10,926
Jesse!

647
00:39:10,927 --> 00:39:14,140
No. You're more my family
than they're my family.

648
00:39:14,141 --> 00:39:15,397
And you're not even my family.

649
00:39:15,398 --> 00:39:17,200
You're just my dad's wife.

650
00:39:17,312 --> 00:39:18,506
Give me the gun.

651
00:39:20,960 --> 00:39:22,022
No way.

652
00:39:22,084 --> 00:39:23,398
Now!

653
00:39:24,638 --> 00:39:25,710
I'm sorry.

654
00:39:26,779 --> 00:39:28,976
You can have the beer,
but...

655
00:39:31,953 --> 00:39:33,196
the gun's mine.